The paper focuses on improving the efficiency and performance of convolutional networks for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of adaptive inference graphs is a novel approach to network architecture, which could also fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Lastly, the paper also touches on the topic of adversarial examples, which is a common area of research in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision.
